snippet: Police officers implicated in the accidental deaths of two teenagers in 2005, which set off a wave of rioting, are expected to stand trial.
abstract: French police officers implicated in 2005 deaths of teenagers Zyed Benna and Bouna Traore, which set off wave of rioting, are expected to stand trial after court overturns a 2011 decision that dismissed the charges.
lead_paragraph: Police officers implicated in the accidental deaths of two teenagers in 2005, which set off a wave of rioting, are expected to stand trial.

headline.seo: France: Officers to Face Trial In Teen Deaths
headline.main: France: Officers Expected to Face Trial in Teen Deaths That Spurred Riots
